<page api="xb">
    <shortlink>api evaluate template function</shortlink>
   <topic>EVALUATE_TEMPLATE Function</topic>
   <description>Evaluate code with optional macros.</description>
   <syntax>C EVALUATE_TEMPLATE(C template[,C Macro1[,...C MacroN]])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>template</name>
         <description>Character</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>Macro1</name>
         <description>Character</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>MacroN</name>
         <description>Character</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <discussion>
EVALUATE_TEMPLATE() executes the Xbasic code specified by Expression. See Code Indirection for more details.

   </discussion>
   
   <sections>
       <section>
       <title>Example</title>
            <description>Assume the variable "command" is set to:  "dim global newVar as C"</description>
            <example><![CDATA[
Evaluate_template(command) -> same as executing the command: "dim global newVar as C"
]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
